Some algae colonies and pollen on water.
Windy- water very choppy.  Chopped weed debris from power boats.

Sunny- light breeze- fishing is poor- no algae is present.
Cloudy- light breeze- no visible algae- 68 degrees.
Clear sky- light breeze- no sign of the resident green ospreys- gang of crows looting ospreys nest- green algae on surface.
Sunny- 10 km breeze from southwest- ice off- 38 degrees.
Cloudy- mostly foggy- dark day.  Light breeze- temp is 59 degrees.
Cloudy- light breeze- air temp 60- some algae and pollen streams
Minor pelagil algal floc.- light breeze- sunny- air temp 69
Cloudy- breezy- no visible algae- air temp 65

No visible algae- light breeze- partly cloudy- .4" rain last night
Partly cloudy- breezy- weed removal- no algae- test secchi same 3.5 Ft reading
Clear sky- light breeze- no visible algae- test secchi disc reading 3'
Overcast- calm- no visible algae- color from bog water- test secchi reading 2.75'

Sunny- light breeze- very slight cloudiness in water- test secchi disc reading 3.0 feet
Overcast- calm- no visible algae- air temp 70
Too many jet skis- noise pollution- some visible algae- nostoc etal- sunny- light breeze
Partly cloudy- air temp 70- small green nostoc coconies visible- light breeze
Partly cloudy- light breeze- no visible algae- air temp 60
Breezy- overcast- no visible algae- air temp 71
Sunny- calm- temp is 34 degrees at 7 am.  Light pelagic floc in shallow water.  Ospreys still present.
Calm- sunny- clear sky.  Light haze of diatoms- in water.
High winds- 15 mph wind- cloudy and overcast- no visible algae- this is my last report.
Sky clear-10 mph wind- no algae- water clean- osprey on nest- 40 degrees.
Light breeze-clear sky- no algae present-water very clean (same depth reading in 5 places) .
Clear sky- 3-5 knot wind- some nostoc colonies present- 70 degrees.
Nostoc bloom- clear sky- 64 degrees- 5 knot wind.
Light breeze- clear sky- no visible algae- 70 degrees.
No algae- clear to partly cloudy- light breeze.
No algae- cloudy- wavy water- light breeze.  67 degrees F.
Sunny-clear sky-light N breeze-no algae-68 degrees F.  As clear blue as light bog tea can look.  You should have a category to cover bog lakes.  Brown might indicate murkiness-loon is not murky.
Partly cloudy- windy- "choppy seas"- no algae-very few aquatic plants visible.  Fine najas on anchor.
No algae visible- sunny-partly cloudy- calm.  68 degrees F.
Clear-light breeze-no algae visible-very few emergent aquatics-63 degrees F.
Overcast- light breeze- no algae- ospreys here but no young reared- 69 degrees F.  First night hawks migrating on 10 August
Overcast- windy- no algae. 66 degrees F.
Overcast- calm- no algae.  79 degrees F.
Sunny-light breeze-no algae visible.  64 degrees F.
Clear-very light breeze-sunny-no algae-bushy pond weed on secchi disc.  Lake color is more golden than brown.  Ospreys not seen for 2 days.
15 knot wind- some white caps-choppy seas-75 degrees f-no algae-partly cloudy-2 bald eagles on osprey island- no ospreys.
Partly cloudy-gusty 15 mph NW wind-52 degrees f-no algae-2 bald eagles on island-osprey near east shore with fish so big it could not take off so it dropped it.
Note: high wind and whitecaps made usual 10-4 reading difficult-so I went late to north island - quiet water north of island.  No algae- 60 degrees F.  One osprey on nest- one on tree.
No algae-20 mph wind northwest-white caps-63 degrees f-partly cloudy-loon near islands last night-sandhill crane fly over mid-week.
Clear-few clouds-planktonic floc present-mostly nostoc-many snails on bottom near shore.
Partly cloudy-calm-planktonic floc. nostoc.  Pine pollen-osprey feed young.  Loon fly over last night-earlier in week 2 visiting ospreys circled the 2 resident ospreys on nest.
Clear sky- light breeze-some planktonic floc-nostoc.  81 degrees F.
Clear sun-light breeze-very light tiny plants-toxic floc-osprey young fledges 24 June.
Scattered strato cumulus-strong breeze-no algae-60 degrees F.
Calm-overcast but bright-no visible planktonic floc.
Light wind-overcast-80 degrees f-no visible algae.
Light wind-some planktonoc floc-clear sky-I am not sure about your color code.  The water is perfectly clear but not blue!  ospreys have three young.

Partly cloudy-no algae-the color of the water on the white section of the disc is clear yellow-I only circle the b because it doesn't fit anywhere else.  It is definitely not brown and none of my readings have ever been brown-time for a change
Rainy- breezy-overcast.  No algae (staff gauge 2.48 14 August) .
Overcast- 15 knot wind- water choppy- no algae.
Read at 19' depth.  Overcast- breezy- no algae visible except for some nostoc balls.
Overcast-no algae-water is colored heavily with bog tannins.  Bald eagle on island.
Clear-light breeze-no algae-light planktonic floc.  Nostoc balls have disappeared.
Overcast-10k wind-choppy water-no algae-67 degrees f-water turbidity from bog tannins.
Ice off 4/20-no algae-20 knot wind-50 degrees f-cloudy-overcast. bald eagles have taken over the osprey nest-carrying sticks.
Sunny- 10k wind northeast- 74 degrees f-some nostoc pelagic floc-vegetative trichomes on surface. eagles + ospreys fighting for territory. no nesting.
Pelagic floc (nostoc- etc.) - sunny- light breeze- osprey eating fish in tree. 2 ospreys at nest this a.m. eagles gone. 81 degrees F.
No algae visible-choppy water-overcast-8k wind se. osprey flew to nest with fish.
Beautiful except for 12 noisy jet skis! pelagic floc-20 knot SW wind-water very choppy-sunny-some clouds- tannins very high. flock of 60 migrating ducks-fish still spawning!
Sunny-light breeze-pelagic floc. very dark tannin water. osprey's at nest but not nesting this year. eagles and ospreys fought over nest-ospreys won but too late to raise young.

No algae visible-light breeze-partly cloudy. due to continuous high water the bog tannins have made the water 69 degrees F. darker than it has ever been + white pines on island are dying off (drowning) .
Very dark tannin water-partly cloudy-15 kt. N wind-choppy-osprey on island.
No algae-light breeze-partly cloudy-no ospreys-raven croaking in morn-beaver dam in outlet channel with 6 inch drop on downstream side.
Clear-slight SW wind-74 degrees f-no algae visible-1 osprey on island.
No algae-5 knot north wind. night hawks migrate 3 September-usually around 25 august. osprey gone-bald eagle on osprey nest.
No algae-5 knot NW wind-52 degrees f-overcast. large snail population-snails increased when we began taking weeds out of lake.
Partly cloudy-northwest wind 5 knots-no algae visible. readings taken after 3/4 mile row with a cracked rib sustained at a disc (Frisbee) golf tourney at Minoqua-"the show must go on!" 57 degrees F.
No algae. sunny.  Some clouds. 44 degrees. sandhill crane calling as it flew over. ospreys on island. night hawks last night.
Overcast - calm - no algae. 55 degrees. ice out on April 15. loons seen by natives on April 20. ospreys nesting.
Clear- sunny-light breeze. moderate nostoc bloom. Bluegills starting to spawn.
Rainy - overcast. some pelagic floc (algae etc.) . SE wind.
Clear day. light 5kt breeze. 68 degrees. abundant algae and other pelagic organisms. osprey young hatched this week on island nest. fishing slow. 2 eagles visited yesterday.
Sunny light breeze. 68 degrees.  Pelagic floc. pine pollen abundant on surface- ospreys feeding young on nest.
Sunny- some clouds. 82 degrees. some pelagic floc. light breeze.
Sunny - partly cloudy- 10 k wind. 72 degrees.  Light pelagic floc. too many jet skis. we traded weeds for snails!
Cloudy. SW wind. light floculant material in water. osprey carrying sticks to nest - toys for young
Partly cloudy 10k easterly wind.  Nostoc aggregates present.  Bluegills and sunfish still have roe!
Partly cloudy - calm. very light pelagic floc. no algae visible.
Partly cloudy - 10k wind 86 degrees. no algae. 3 young osprey fledged this week.
Partly cloudy. 5kt wind. no algae. 72 degrees.
Light breeze. partly cloudy. 63 degrees. no pelagic algae- but we have an abundance of filamentous algae on lake aquatics on bottom of lake. night hawks migrated august 18.
Raining. light breeze. overcast. no algae blooms. some nostoc aggregates + gleocapsa. some filamentous algae on aquatic plants.
15 knot wind. cloud cover 75%. no algae- water choppy.
Light breeze. 60 degrees. clouds - cirro-cumulus and cirrostratus. no algae.
Overcast and light drizzle.  Calm. no algae.  Osprey caught fish 100 feet from my boat - what a sight!.  This will be my last report for 1997.
Cloudy SE wind at 10 kt 72 degrees. no algae loon on island.
Cloudy SE breeze 70 degrees.  Pelagic floc.
Sunny E wind at 8 kt. 68 degrees.  No algae willow and cottonwood hairy.
Partly cloudy NW wind at 15 kt. thunderstorm last night raised level.  No algae.
Partly cloudy light breeze 53 degrees. osprey hatched 6/1/98.  Beaver dam in.
Partly cloudy light breeze 74 degrees. May have Eurasian Watermilfoil.
Partly cloudy SW wind at 10 kt. 87 degrees. no algae. loon on west shore 8 in the evening. 6/19.
Overcast light breeze 72 degrees. no algae.
Clear 5 kt. wind 76 degrees. no algae.
Clear 5 kt. wind 80 degrees. no algae.  Osprey near fledging.
Clear light breeze. no algae. osprey ready to fledge.
Clear light breeze 70 degrees. no algae. ospreys have fledged.
Sunny light breeze 78 degrees. no algae.
Rainy all wee 5 kt. wind 82 degree.  No algae.
Clear 5 kt. wind 66 degrees.  No algae.  Osprey soaring.
Overcast light breeze 73 degrees.  No algae.
Sunny NW wind at 12 kt. 78 degrees. no algae.
Light breeze 73 degrees. some nostoc globules and male vallisneria flowers.  1 osprey.
Sunny light breeze 75 degrees.  Nostoc globules.
Rainy calm 70 degrees. no algae.  1 adult eagle and 1 juvenile.
Cloudy- wind at five mph- no algae- and ospreys on nest of their own making.  The temperature is 55 degrees.
East wind at five mph- cottonwood hairs on surface- osprey near nest- two mallards in tree- eight fishing boats on the south side of lake- and the temperature is 63 degrees F.
Clear- southeast wind at 10 mph- pelagic floc- veg. trichomes on surface- some nostoc floating near shore with pine pollen- and the temperature is 83 degrees F.

Overcast- calm- spirogyra colonies on aquatics- 16 canadian geese flew over- ospry flying with large branch- two wood ducks in large pine tree- and green heron on island.  The temperature is 68 degrees.
Mostly cloudy- southwest wind at 7 mph- no algae- and no pelagics.  The temperature is 70 degrees.
Thin overcast- southwest wind at 10 mph- no algae- and osprey on island nest feeding young.  The temperature is 76 degrees.
Partly cloudy- sunny- no algae- south wind at 10mph- young ospreys visible in nest- and eagle flying on east shore.  The temperature is 86 degrees.
Overcast- no aglae- west wind at 5 mph- and we had 8.5 inches of rain since last saturday.  The temperature is 72 degrees.
Overcast- east wind at 5 mph- no visible algae- water darkened by bog runoff of 9.5" rain- and the temperature is 70 degrees.
Intermittent cloudiness- some sun- scattered showers- southe wind at 10 mph- N o algae- and 13.5" of rain in fifteen days.  The temperature is 78 degrees.
Overcast- NW 5kt wind- no algae- young ospreys test wings on nest- one flying in place on nest. 68 F.
Partly cloudy- 10kt wind- no algae- loon calling yesterday- robins on 3rd hatch!  76 F.
Partly cloudy- sunny- 5kt SW wind- no algae- loon calling- weed harvesting this week- 79 F-
Partly cloudy- 10kt NW wind- no algae- nighthawks start migrating 8/16/99- 4 ospreys soaring- beaver dam in outlet channel.  68 F.
Scattered clouds- 5kt NW wind- no algae- wem seeds forming- 2 ospreys- 15 canada geese- beaver dam removed.  63 F
Sunny. hazy. no algae. SW  kt wind. lone loon in winter phase on 3 sept 99.  Also 30 cormorants. 87 F.
Sunny. light breeze. some white pelagic floc. 3 ospreys on island. no algae. 62 F

Clear. 5k NW wind. no algae. 8 immature cormorants on island 09/28.  Ospreys last seen 9/22. 54 F.

10kt NW wind.  Mostly cloudy- some sun- no algae.  Birds attacking eagle at nest-pecking on it's head.  Young eagle flashes wing in nest. 60 degrees F.
10kt SW wind- no algae.  Bald eagle flying and one on nest with young- young eagle pledged yesturday. 20 cormorants flying.  Blue gills biting- four boats fishing north islant.  80 degrees F.
10kt SW wind- partly cloudy- sunny- no algae.  Young eagle hunkers down- adult at nest. 69 degrees F.
Clear- sunny- 5kt NW wind- no algae.  Young eagle flies from nest to branch and returns to nest.  Flies above nest but does not venture far.  Loon on lake on 6/25.
Light overcast.  3kt SE wind.  No algae.  Loon visitor 7/1.  Beaver dam partly open.  Group of 3 ospreys fly over.  Young eagle flies over lake.
Clear- 5kt SW wind.  Young eagle on island- old eagle chased by 2 ospreys.  No algae.  Ewm ln eevils put in on 7/6.  84 degrees F.
Overcast- 5kt wind- no algae.  Old eagle and young in white pine on island.
Partly cloudy- partly sunny.  5kt NE wind.  No algae.  Young eagle back on nest.
Overcast- no algae- 5kt southwest wind- and eagles- adult and young on island.  The temperature is 71 degrees F.
Clear- sunny- calm- no algae- vallisheria and ewm in bloom- young eagle ones- osprey chases eagle- and the temperature is 74 degrees F.
High cirrus-strato clouds- sunny- light southwest breeze- no algae- two ospreys high over island- adult and young eagles in trees on island (decodon in bloom) .  The temperature is 70 degrees F.

Few scattered strato cumulus clouds- 64 degrees F.- calm- pelagic floc- some nostoc- male flowers of vallisheria on surface- ewm miofoil weevil survey on 8/22- adult eagle on island- young eating fish on nest- and loon on lake on 8/25/00.
Partly cloudy- 5kt southeast wind- some pelagic floc- no algae- loon on lake on 8/28/00- and night hawks migrate on 8/25/00.  The temperature is 70 degrees F.
Clear- 10kt east wind- some pelagic floc- and on 9/3/00 there was 3" inches of rain.  The temperature is 65 degrees F.
Partly cloudy- 5kt south wind- no algae- young eagle on island- and adult on east shore of lake.  The temperature is 70 degrees F.
Partly cloudy- 10kt northwest wind- no algae- and 5" inches of rain this week.  The temperature is 58 degrees F.
Overcast- 5kt east wind- no algae- pied billed grebes and cormurants on lake- and adult bald eagle on 9/20/00.  The temperature is 52 degrees F.
Sunny with scattered strato cumulus clouds- calm- scattered nostoc floc and beaver dam in outlet channel. last reading for the the year- back to mn for the winter.  The temperature is 58 degrees F.
Sunny- clear- 5 knot north wind- no algae- and ospreys nesting on island.  The temperature is 56 degrees F.

Partly sunny- strato cumulus clouds- southeast four knot wind- no algae- crew from milfoil putting buoys to mark areas where beetles were introduced for eurasian water milfoil control.  The temperature is 60 degrees F.
Overcast- northwest five knot wind- rainy- no algae- white pelagic floc- bog water from recent rain results in light brown color of water.  The temperature is 51 degrees F.
Clear- northwest wind at 15 knots- no green algae- white pelagic floc- bog tea water- nine sandhill cranes fly over- and the temperature is 72 degrees F.
Scattered strato cumulus clouds- southwest wind at 10 knot- no algae- small bass biting on north side- and two ospreys on nest on island.
Clear sky- five knot southwest wind- no algae- light pelagic floc- 20 ospreys at nest- 2 otters on east shore.  The temperature is 69.8 degrees F.
Partly cloudy- high cirrus clouds- light west breeze- no algae (generally)- but some spirogyra near shore on emergents- loon on lake 6/29.  The temperature is 80 degrees F.
Clear- four knot southwest wind- white pelagic floc- no green algae- loon flying over and calling at 4:30 am- loon on lake 7/7.  The temperature is 82 degrees F.
Partly cloudy- high cirro-cumulus clouds- three knot southwest wind- no algae- young osprey fledged- and loon calling on 7/11.  The temperature is 74 degrees F.
Partly cloudy- strato cumulus clouds- three knot northeast wind- no algae- two young ospreys flying.  The temperature is 74 degrees F.
Overcast. 5 knot NW wind. Squall line. Light rain- no algae. 78 deg F.
Wispy high cirrus clouds. Hazy. 8 knot SW wind. Nostoc bloom this week- flaky colonies. 82 deg F
Clear- 10 knot NW wind. No algae. Light pelagic floc. Rained on 8-15 and 8-16. 68 deg F
Clear- light breeze. Ubiquitous nostoc flocculate. Cormorants roosting on island. Nighthawks migrating. Ospreys on island. Rain all day 8-25. 74 deg F
Clear- 10 knot SW wind. Sparse pelagic flocculate. 4 cormorants on island. 25 last night.
Overcast stratocumulus. 5 knot SW wind. No algae. 3 cormorants on island. 66 deg F
Stratus overcast. Calm- no algae. 2 adult bald eagles and 2 cormorants on island. 64 deg F
Stratocumulus- 15 knot N wind. No algae. Bald eagle at osprey nest. Pied billed grebes on lake. 51 deg F.
Strato-cumulus overcast. 5 knot N wind. No algae. 1 cormorant on island. 30 goose flock overhead. 50 F
DEEPEST POINT OF LAKE - 1FT OFF BOTTOM
Overcast with a light SE breeze. 24 cormorants on island. Flock of 50 flew overhead. 5/26/02- Rained all day through this morning. 2 ospreys on island.
Clear- sunny weather. SW winds at 5 knots. White Pelabic Flock. 1 osprey on nest- 1 flying over island.
Overcast- light breeze. No algae. 1 Osprey at nest on island-maybe attending young.
Clear- sunny weather. NW winds at 8 knots. Ospreys on island nest tending young.
High- thin clouds and sunny. SW winds at 10 knots. No algae and EWM is abundant.
Weather is hazy and sunny. SW winds at 5 knots. No algae. 2 loons on lake last night. 3 juvenile ospreys on island nest.
Alto stratus clouds- partly sunny and no wind. No algae and EWM is rampant. High amount of bog tea in the water.
Clear- light NW breeze. No algae. 3 young ospreys flapping wings. Pontederia in bloom. EWM is abundant.
Clear and sunny. No algae. 2 young ospreys still on nest. 1 fledged 7/14/02.
Hazy- W winds at 5 knots. No algae. All young ospreys have flown off the nest.
Few scattered clouds and a light breeze. No algae. Tornado Storm 7/31/02.
Scattered cumulus clouds- 5 knot SW wind- no algae- one adult and three young ospreys in trees on island.
Clear sky- sunny- 10 knot west wind- no algae- four ospreys on island- great egret on west shore- and 60 knot wind storm on 8/17/02.
Partly cloudy- strato cumulus clouds- 10 knot west wind- no algae- three ospreys on island.
Partly cloudy- cumulus high cirrus clouds- S wind at 8kts- no algae- two ospreys - osprey attacks bald eagle and eagle turns over to grab osprey - nymphaea and nuphar invading EWM beds.
Clear- 5kt wind SW- no algae- white pelagic floc- bald eagle on west island- two ospreys- and one blue heron.
Clear- 4kt NE wind- no algae- bald eagle on west island- and one osprey on east end.
Overcast- no algae- 10 knot NW wind- ospreys gone- two bald eagles on lakeshore and one bald eagle flyover.
Partly cloudy- high cirro stratus clouds- 4 knot NE wind- red maples just this week coloring on west shore- and no eagles or ospreys.  Last Reading of the Season!
Cirro-cumulus- 2 knot east wind. No algae. East and west island osprey nests. Both occupied - 4 ospreys present.
Clear- no algae. 5 knot N wind. Osprey flyover. 2 ospreys on west nest. EWM red tips showing 1 ft. below surface.
Clear- no algae. White pelagic floc. 5 knot S wind. 5 cormorants- 2 green herons.
Strato cumulus. Calm- no algae. EWM treated 6/02. 2 loons on south side. 100 geese flyover. EWM looks sick.
Sunny- 8 knot NE wind. No algae. White pelagic floc. EWM has stopped growing. Ospreys feed young both nests.
Clear- light breeze- no algae. White pelagic floc. Loon flyover- crazy call.
Partly sunny. Strato-cumulus clouds. 8 knot west wind. No algae. Loon call 8 AM. Water clean- no floc. EWM sinking after 2-4-D.
Thin cloud layer. SE 5 knot wind. No algae. Loon on west end of island. Mournful cry- loon flyover.
Scattered strato-cumulus- 20 knot SW wind. No algae. Loon north of island.
Sunny- 15 knot north wind. No algae. Young ospreys testing wings above the East Island nest.
Overcast- cumulus clouds. Light sprinkle. 5 knot S wind. No algae. 1 loon north of the island.
Overcast- strato-cumulus. 5 knot wind to the north. NO algae. Loon flyover. Shower at 2:15.
Hazy- 10 knot west wind. No algae. 3 out of 8 ospreys present on island.
High cirrus and cirro cumulus. 4 knot east wind. Some nostoc colonies. White pelagic floc.
High cirro-stratus. Halo (aura) around sun. Light SW breeze. Some nostoc and white pelagic floc. 4 ospreys present
Light overcast- foggy stratus. Calm. Some algae. White pelagic floc. 1 osprey still here.
Low stratus- overcast. 8 knot wind. No algae. 5 inches of rain in last 3 days. 1 osprey on island.
Strato-cumulus- overcast. SW 5 knot wind. Loon fly over island. Osprey on east island nest.  Algae present.  44 F.
Alto cirrus.  Sunny.  24 knot SW wind.  Massive nostoc bloom. White floc on surface.  Ospreys on east and west nests on island.  Loon on nest.  64 F
Overcast.  Strato cumulus.  7 knot SW wind.  Nostoc and white floc.  Ospreys feeding on both nests.  Loon on nest.  SW side of island.   50 F.
Sunny- 7 knot NW wind.  Nostoc and pelagic floc.  Bald eagle.  Ospreys on both nests.  Loon on nest. 43 F
Strato cumulus.  5 knot NW wind.  No algae.  Loon hatched - young 6/28/04.  Female loon on nest.
High cirrus. Sunny. Light breeze.  No algae.  Loon call oo-waa.  First time loons nested. 50 F.
Sunny- 7 knot SW wind.  Nostoc bloom. 60F.
High cirrus and alto cumulus.  Sunny.  5 knot SE wind.  No algae. 60 F
Strato-cumulus.  10 knot NW wind.  Sunny- no algae. 74 F.
High thin layer of cirro-cumulus-stratus.  Sunny- calm.  No algae.  Dead osprey - lightning struck nest.  Picked by crow.
Clear- calm- sunny.  Nostoc bloom.  Pelagic white floc.  Other algae.
Clear- sunny- 17 knot west wind.  No algae.
Alto-stratus and strato cumulus.  S knot northwind.  No algae.  Young loon full grown.
Scattered strato-cumulus- sunny- 4 knot south wind.  No algae.  Young loon raised out of water.  Flew a few feet.  82 F.
Alto-cirrus and strato cumulus-4 knots SW wind- no algae- osprey- nest with young- East Island
Cirro cumulus and strato cumulus- hazy sun- loon on nest on SW tip of island- no algae- two osprey nests on east island.
sunny- a few strato-cumulus SW 5-knot wind- white pelagic floc- and some green algae. 2loons
strato cumulus overcast- 5 knot SE wind- no algae
strato cumulus overcast- calm- no algae- 2 loons west shore- 70F
few light high cirrus- 5 knot south wind- no algae- one loon east lake
sunny clear 5 knot SW wind. no algae at sight.
light breeze- cirrocumulus clouds- no algae- 2 adult and three osprey young on east island nest
strato-cumulus 8- knota wets wind. (Beautort scale) no algae-myriads of male vallisneria flowers on surface of water.
a few alto stratus- light SW breeze- no algae- male vallisneria flowers on surface of water.
thin stratus clouds- light S. breeze- male vallisneria flowers on surface- 70F
strato-cumulus 5 knot north wind- no algae- osprey still present on island nest- 62F
a few stcattered strato-cumulus- calm- no algae
clear- calm- no algae- some white pelagic floc- one osprey
